race.comment: Tough race. THE MARG FACTOR (8) doesn't win out of turn but her past two have been good at Mornington, behind a progressive one last time in this grade. From barrier one, she'll go straight to the front and should take catching around this circuit. SHE NAILED IT (12) is off a short break here and up in trip which is some query but her best form is at this trip, even boasting a fifth to Treasurethe Moment at 200-1 last time in at Flemington. GAME PLAN (6) resumed with a tidy win on wet ground at Ballarat over 1200m, running on strongly from back in the field. Quickly to 1600m here but has come back well. LA ROSETTA (14) was a bit better second up when backed at Wangaratta and should be at peak fitness now. She sets up well for Celine Gaudray from the gate. REAL ALLIANCE (11) is third up off a solid win in easier company and can measure up.
